<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/7257685-karen"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/7257685-karen">Karen</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I think it&apos;s not a trend, just a question of taste. The length worked great for me. When I like a book, I don&apos;t want it to end! And I love detail.<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I think it's not a trend, just a question of taste. The length worked great for me. When I like a book, I don't want it to end! And I love detail.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
