<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/141867-i-don-t-understand-it-says-that-it-will">I don&#39;t understand. It says that it will be published in September 16 and today is the 5th, but there are already reviews down here from a couple of months ago. What is going on?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_141867'><a id="like_count_community_question_141867" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/141867?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F20821087-the-paying-guests">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/141867-i-don-t-understand-it-says-that-it-will">7 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/141867-i-don-t-understand-it-says-that-it-will">See all 10 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/28363483-dawn-stowell"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1639841523i/28363483._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/28363483-dawn-stowell">Dawn Stowell</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Some people have access to ARC (Advance Reader&apos;s Copy) or something similar. This is when publishers make available copies available ahead of the rele<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Some people have access to ARC (Advance Reader's Copy) or something similar. This is when publishers make available copies available ahead of the release date of their books as part of a PR (public relations) move to promote sales of their books by taking a chance that the book they are offering will garner more good reviews than bad and in doing so will encourage more sales of the book.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
