<div id="review_1081425605" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1081425605" />
    <a title="Felicity Allan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36002713-felicity-allan"><img alt="Felicity Allan" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1081425605?book_show_action=true">Oct 16, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Felicity Allan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Felicity Allan" href="/user/show/36002713-felicity-allan">Felicity Allan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1081425605" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13865064632309893327">Groosly overwriten and cliched, the most glaring deficiency is a complete lack of firm, sympathetic editing. Key scenes, when they eventually arrive, are marred by repetition, bad use of adjectives and seriously poor punctuation.<br/><br/>The main protagonists are completely two dimensional, particularly the ghastly, flaccid Lilian, and there is a passage in serious contention for the Bad Sex prize.<br/><br/>The narrative is very obviously a close copy of &apos;A Pin To See The Peepshow&apos;, which is sad given Sarah Waters</span>
  <span id="freeText13865064632309893327" style="display:none">Groosly overwriten and cliched, the most glaring deficiency is a complete lack of firm, sympathetic editing. Key scenes, when they eventually arrive, are marred by repetition, bad use of adjectives and seriously poor punctuation.<br /><br />The main protagonists are completely two dimensional, particularly the ghastly, flaccid Lilian, and there is a passage in serious contention for the Bad Sex prize.<br /><br />The narrative is very obviously a close copy of 'A Pin To See The Peepshow', which is sad given Sarah Waters' former originality. It has all the hallmarks of a book laboured over under contract. Ms Waters should be allowed ten years if she needs it.<br /><br />A bad and exhausting read.<br /><br />FMA</span>
  <a data-text-id="13865064632309893327" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
